The article discusses the importance of art therapy in treating veterans with PTSD, TBI, and other psychological health conditions. It highlights the Creative Forces Summit, an initiative by the National Endowment of the Arts (NEA) in partnership with the U.S. Department of Defense and Veterans Affairs, that places creative arts therapies at the core of patient-centered care at military medical facilities across the country. The article also mentions the inspirational stories of veterans who have benefitted from art therapy, such as Chris Stowe, who teaches glass blowing to vets in Florida. Additionally, it mentions the opening of a new art therapy area at the James A. Haley Veterans Hospital and a telehealth program in Gainesville that allows veterans in rural communities to receive the benefits of art therapy. The author expresses their honor in having a platform to promote art therapy and encourages readers to follow their visits across the United States and around the world to elevate the importance of art therapy.